      <acqinfo encodinganalog="541">
         <head>Provenance</head>
         <p> The papers of James Whitcomb Riley, author and poet,
were given to the Library of Congress by Nelson R. Burr in 1957.  Additional material was
purchased by the Library in 1996 and 1998.</p>
      </acqinfo>
      <processinfo encodinganalog="583">
         <head>Processing History</head>
         <p>The papers of James Whitcomb Riley were arranged and described in 1997.  Additional material received in 1998 was incorporated into the collection in 2000.</p>
      </processinfo>
